            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "oh this is cool, good idea! this is a natural addition to the `vim.pos` toolkit. though i assume it doesn't close https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36331 because:\r\n\r\n> one might be interested in finding the closest code action/inlay-hint/LSP reference to the cursor\r\n\r\nbecause 2 byte offsets might have a delta of 1, but if one is at (line1,col999) and the other at (line2,col1), they will be visually \"far apart\" in terms of \"Manhattan distance\".\r\n\r\nwould appreciate feedback from @Davidyz \r\n",
